  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 32000 0
  MOD DUMMY1 PER
  IFVAR DUMMY1 > 120
    ECHO PLAYER You found a hidden trail!
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
Number 3018
Name Caldis Forest, Thick Vines
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
IFENTRY -1
        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
ENDIF
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Thick undergrowth slows your passage through here as you carefully select
your footing. Snarling vines and hidden rocks create an obstacle course
for any choosing this path. The trees are sparse here, giving you abundant
light to get by.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3014
EXIT E 3019
;
Number 3019
Name Caldis Forest, Uneasiness
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Elm and maple branches thicken above you, blotting out most of the light,
giving the forest an evil look. White bony birch trees stretch out around
you as you walk further into its ribcage. A brisk breeze whistles through
the tree tops, rocking them back and forth and you can hear the sound of
deadwood creaking in the distance.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3018
EXIT SW 3023
EXIT S 3024
;
Number 3020
Name Caldis Forest, Stream
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The ground becomes soft under your feet as you travel closer to the stream.
You can hear the  rushing water off to the east as you make you way down
the trail. The air around you is moist and you can smell the rich pine trees
growing near by. The trail only leads back the way you came.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 3025
ITEM 0 694 ADJ3=1251 VAL5=2
;
Number 3021
Name Caldis Forest, Mysterious Rocks
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Scattered throughout this area are large stones, with symbols chiseled into
them. Rock chips and dust on the ground leads you to guess that this act
was recently done. Looking at the symbols, you can not even fathom a guess
as to what they stand for. In the distance, you hear the hoot of an owl.
*DESCRIPTION_END
