Number 3022
Name Caldis Forest, Body
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You see the remains of a rusted sword laying in the grip of a human skeleton
half reclining against a tree. Its bones, stark white and completely picked
of all skin and meat are beginning to show signs of deterioration. The path
brings you to the west and the southwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3021
EXIT SW 3026
ITEM 0 390
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
There is a horizontal cut across the top of the skull.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 3023
Name Caldis Forest, Underbrush
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
IFENTRY -1
        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
ENDIF
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The thick underbrush begins to thin out now, and walking becomes much easier.
Several types of colorful flowers push up around the base of a few rocks and
trees. A pair of hummingbirds float from flower to flower, bud to bud in
their daily routine, before  flying out of sight down the path. Forking out
in front of you, the trail goes northeast or south.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 3019
EXIT S 3028
;
Number 3024
Name Caldis Forest, Canopy
FOREST
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tall thin birch trees mixed with uquart and maples cover these parts as you
continue down. Contrary to the bark size,  the branches above are thick and
woven together.  It is hard to tell the time of day here because of the lack
of light. The air has an earthly scent to it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3019
EXIT SW 3028
;
Number 3025
Name Caldis Forest, Moss
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Large stretches of ground here are covered in a soft green moss, fed by the
stream near by. A small brook meanders away from its tributary interrupting
your path. With care, you can manage your way across by stepping on the
rocks. This area is ideal to lie down and stretch out with its pleasing scenery.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3020
EXIT SW 3029
;
Number 3026
Name Caldis Forest, Rows of Oak
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Huge oak trees line your path like sentries standing at attention as you walk
on by. These wooden soldier like trees give you a sense of security, knowing
how old they must be. The bark is smooth to the touch like fine new leather
armor. Besides a few fallen leaves, the path is perfectly clear of rubble,
and continues to the south.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 3022
EXIT E 3027
EXIT S 3031
;
Number 3027
Name Caldis Forest, Near the Eltinmar
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Through the thinning forest, you see the banks of the Eltinmar, and the swift
water of the river itself. There are a variety of trees here, both common
and otherwise. Some small scrub bushes provide ground cover for the animals.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3026
EXIT S 3032
;
Number 3028
Name Caldis Forest, Overgrown Trail
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
IFENTRY -1
        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
ENDIF
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Traveling slows to a crawl as you push through the overgrown trail. The
shadows around you play with your imagination and an eerie screech from
an vulture can be heard from above you. Continuing on, one foot in front of
the other, you try to escape this uncertain neck of the woods.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3023
EXIT NE 3024
EXIT E 3029
;
Number 3029
Name Caldis Forest, Variety
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This area is at the center of some rather varied terrain. The western
side of this area of forest is thick with vines, which thin quickly. Near
the northern section, small patches of moss grow in, tribute to the lush
ground beneath and everywhere else around you, there are young trees that
are mostly maple and uquart growing stolidly.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3028
EXIT NE 3025
EXIT E 3030
;
Number 3030
Name Caldis Forest, Thin Forest
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
There is almost no vegetation or signs of life around you as the trail
continues. Medium tall trees stand separate from each other creating a
lot of airy space. The ground beneath your feet is a deep and spongy
loam, all that is left of the trees that no longer stand.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3029
EXIT E 3031
ITEM 0 80 VAL2=3034
;
Number 3031
Name Caldis Forest, Lightning Strike
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here, a blackened area circle shaped contrasts greatly with the greenery
around it. With the split of one tree you can tell it was caused by lightning.
Soot and ash float in the air from the recent burnout. Remarkably, the fire
did not spread any further than it did, but was probably stopped by the stream
that flows from the northwest to the east from here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3030
EXIT N 3026
EXIT E 3032
;
Number 3032
Name Caldis Forest, Stream
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 8
MONSTER_GROUP 35
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A stream flows in from the west, to the east, going south of the kvantar
forest, undoubtedly to join with the Eltinmar River about half a mile
downstream. The water makes the air moist and the ground slightly damp.
There are trails leading west, paralleling the stream, and north. From
a small rise here, you can see the very tip of the kvantar construction.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3031
EXIT N 3027
;
